KPMG Intl names Colin Sharman as chairman . KPMG International on Wednesday said it named Colin Sharman , senior partner of the firm ' s U . K . practice , as its new chairman . Sharman succeeds Jon Madonna , who steps down January 31 from the post of international chairman , a position he has held since October 1995 . Madonna is joining Travelers Group Inc as a vice chairman . The largest professional services firm said Sharman , 53 , will remain U . K . senior partner , a position he has held for the past three years . 
